This executive order, issued by President Donald J. Trump on May 1, 2020, declares a national emergency with respect to the threat to the United States bulk-power system. The order aims to protect the security, integrity, and reliability of the bulk-power system by prohibiting certain transactions involving bulk-power system electric equipment. The order prohibits the acquisition, importation, transfer, or installation of such equipment by any person, or with respect to any property, subject to the jurisdiction of the United States, if the equipment is designed, developed, manufactured, or supplied by persons owned by, controlled by, or subject to the jurisdiction or direction of foreign adversaries. The order also authorizes the Secretary of Energy to take necessary actions to implement the order and establishes a Task Force on Federal Energy Infrastructure Procurement Policies Related to National Security. The Task Force will work to protect the nation from national security threats through the coordination of federal government procurement of energy infrastructure. The order includes definitions of key terms and provides for recurring and final reports to Congress regarding the national emergency.